  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_and_care_professions_council">Health and Care Professions Council</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_regulatory_body">Regulatory Body</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_and_care_professions_council">Health and Care Professions Council</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_and_care_professions_council">HCPC</xref>
) is an independent, United Kingdom wide professional regulator, which sets standards of professional training, skills, behaviour and health of the professions they regulate.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_and_care_professions_council">Health and Care Professions Council</xref>
 works to protect the health and well-being of people using the services of the health, social work and psychological professionals registered with them.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_and_care_professions_council">Health and Care Professions Council</xref>
 regulates the following professions:  </p>
